  <li>How to format <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51313127/jekyll-inserting-extra-code-when-generating-blog-posts">code</a> snippets.</li>
</ul>

<p>Run the command from that directory to compile and run your site locally to test - <br />
<code class="highlighter-rouge">terminal
bundle exec jekyll serve
</code> <br />
Documentation:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://jekyllrb.com/tutorials/using-jekyll-with-bundler/">bundle</a></li>
  <li></li>
</ul>

<p>You can then test your site locally - typically this address with ll be http://127.0.0.1:4000/ <br /></p>

<p>Setting up <code class="highlighter-rouge">jekyll</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">GitHub Pages</code> only required basic programming skills and beginner Github experience.  I would recommend using GitHub Pages for your personal site.</p>

